2.3.48.1 Program Scope and Objectives
Command Code UPDIS for the GUF System 2.3.48 page
Scope and (
) This section gives step-by-step guidance for the display and retrieval of un- postable information for IDRS (Integrated Data Retrieval System) Command Code UPDIS. (
) Purpose: This transmits IRM
, IDRS Terminal Responses, Command Code UPDIS. (
) Audience: All IRS business units. (
) Program Owner: AD/Submission Processing (
) Primary Stakeholders: Wage & Investment (W&I), Large & Mid-Size Business (LMSB), Small Business Self Employed (SBSE), Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/GE) (

) Program Goals: Command Code (CC) UPDIS accesses the GUF-AREA data base and displays a requested unpostable case for a speciﬁc sequence number. Command Code UPDIS also accesses the GUF-TIN-AREA to determine whether other cases exist with the same TIN. CC UPDIS must be used prior to CC UPCAS, CC UPRES and CC UPREV.
